About.Name: Francesco De Lorenzo
About.AboutText:
Hi I am Francesco De Lorenzo Im a Senior in electrical engineering. Currently, I am pursuing my undergraduate degree at Seattle Pacific University. I am dedicated to expanding my knowledge and skills in various areas of Electrical Engineering, with a particular focus on circuitry and R&D. I thrive in collaborative environments where I can contribute my expertise and learn from my peers.

I believe in the importance of continuous learning and seek out opportunities to explore new technologies and methodologies.

Project1.Title: Bandpass Sallen Key IR Detector
Project1.Desc: This is the assembled circuit on a breadboard, which successfully filters out all prequencies but 10kHz, then using a peak detector will find the peak voltage and run that into a comparator to signal an LED to turn on when the correct frequency is passed.

Project2.Title: Junior Design Project: FPV Drone
Project2.Desc: This project had us design a drone chassis and calculate the proper battery size for a high-speed FPV drone. We worked in cross-disciplinary teams to create a functional prototype.

Project3.Title: Senior Design Project: Backcountry Smartwatch
Project3.Desc: This project is based on designing a quad sensor digital watch that can sense your altitude, temperature, barometric pressure, incline, and a compass. It will be displayed on a small graphical LCD display in a waterproof CNC'd aluminum housing.
